permissibleValues.meaningDescription: The area between the x-axis and the curve given by the integrand. It is equal to the definite integral of a function. In the field of pharmacokinetics, the area under the curve (AUC) is the area under the curve in a plot of concentration of a drug in plasma against time. AUC is usually given for the time interval zero to infinity, and other time intervals are indicated.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: The area between the x-axis and the curve given by the integrand. It is equal to the definite integral of a function. In the field of pharmacokinetics, the area under the curve (AUC) is the area under the curve in a plot of concentration of a drug in plasma against time. AUC is usually given for the time interval zero to infinity, and other time intervals are indicated.
The metric unit of absorbed radiation dose equal to the absorption of one hundredth of joule of radiation energy per kilogram of matter.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: Grams per day.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: Grams per day.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A metric unit of areal density defined as a spread rate at which one gram of a substance is spread over the area of one square meter. It is equal to approximately 0.029 4935 ounce per square yard. Also used as a dose calculation unit to express quantity of an agent in grams per body surface area in square meters.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A metric unit of areal density defined as a spread rate at which one gram of a substance is spread over the area of one square meter. It is equal to approximately 0.029 4935 ounce per square yard. Also used as a dose calculation unit to express quantity of an agent in grams per body surface area in square meters.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A dose administration rate unit equal to the rate at which a gram of a product is delivered or administered over the time period of one week. This is also a unit of mass flow rate equivalent to the rate at which a gram of matter crosses a given surface or is delivered to a given object or space over a period of time equal to one week.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A dose administration rate unit equal to the rate at which a gram of a product is delivered or administered over the time period of one week. This is also a unit of mass flow rate equivalent to the rate at which a gram of matter crosses a given surface or is delivered to a given object or space over a period of time equal to one week.
A unit of radioactivity equal to one thousandth of a curie or 37 megabecquerels, and corresponding to a radioactivity of 37 millions of atomic disintegrations per second.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A unit of relative amount of a substance equal to one thousandth of an equivalent weight.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A unit of relative amount of a substance equal to one thousandth of an equivalent weight.
A measure of weight.  A milligram is approximately 450,000 times smaller than a pound and 28,000 times smaller than an ounce.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A unit of mass flow rate equivalent to the rate at which one thousandth of a gram of matter crosses a given surface or is delivered to a given object or space over a period of time equal to twenty four hours. Milligram per twenty four hours is also a dose administration rate unit equal to the rate at which one thousandth of a gram of a product is administered per unit of time equal to twenty four hours.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A unit of mass flow rate equivalent to the rate at which one thousandth of a gram of matter crosses a given surface or is delivered to a given object or space over a period of time equal to twenty four hours. Milligram per twenty four hours is also a dose administration rate unit equal to the rate at which one thousandth of a gram of a product is administered per unit of time equal to twenty four hours.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one milligram of a substance in unit volume of the mixture equal to one cubic deciliter or 100 cubic centimeters. It is also a unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one milligram occupies the volume one cubic deciliter or 100 cubic centimeters.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one milligram of a substance in unit volume of the mixture equal to one cubic deciliter or 100 cubic centimeters. It is also a unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one milligram occupies the volume one cubic deciliter or 100 cubic centimeters.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A unit of mass flow rate equivalent to the rate at which one thousandth of a gram of matter crosses a given surface or is delivered to a given object or space over a period of time equal to one hour.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A unit of mass flow rate equivalent to the rate at which one thousandth of a gram of matter crosses a given surface or is delivered to a given object or space over a period of time equal to one hour.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A unit of a mass fraction expressed as a number of milligrams of substance per kilogram of mixture. The unit is also used as a dose calculation unit.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A unit of a mass fraction expressed as a number of milligrams of substance per kilogram of mixture. The unit is also used as a dose calculation unit.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A dose calculation unit expressed in milligram(s) per kilogram per period of time equal to twenty-four hours.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A dose calculation unit expressed in milligram(s) per kilogram per period of time equal to twenty-four hours.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A metric unit of areal density equal to approximately 2.94935E-5 ounce per square yard. Also used as a dose calculation unit.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A metric unit of areal density equal to approximately 2.94935E-5 ounce per square yard. Also used as a dose calculation unit.

permissibleValues.shortMeaning: Milligram per Square Meter per Day
permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A dose calculation unit expressed in milligram(s) per square meter per period of time equal to twenty-four hours.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A dose calculation unit expressed in milligram(s) per square meter per period of time equal to twenty-four hours.

permissibleValues.shortMeaning: Milligram per Square Meter per Week
permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A dose calculation unit expressed in milligram(s)per square meter per period of time equal to seven days.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A dose calculation unit expressed in milligram(s)per square meter per period of time equal to seven days.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one milligram occupies the volume one milliliter.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A SI derived unit of mass concentration defined as the concentration of one kilogram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one cubic meter, or the concentration of one milligram of a substance per unit volume of the mixture equal to one milliliter, or one gram of a substance per one liter of the mixture. It is also a unit of mass density (volumic mass) defined as the density of substance which mass equal to one milligram occupies the volume one milliliter.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A dose administration rate unit equal to the rate at which one thousandth of a gram of a product is delivered or administered over the time period of one week. This is also a unit of mass flow rate equivalent to the rate at which one thousandth of a gram of matter crosses a given surface or is delivered to a given object or space over a period of time equal to one week.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A dose administration rate unit equal to the rate at which one thousandth of a gram of a product is delivered or administered over the time period of one week. This is also a unit of mass flow rate equivalent to the rate at which one thousandth of a gram of matter crosses a given surface or is delivered to a given object or space over a period of time equal to one week.

A measure of volume for a liquid.  A milliliter is approximately 950 times smaller than a quart and 30 times smaller than a fluid ounce.  A milliliter of liquid and a cubic centimeter (cc) of liquid are the same.
A unit of amount of substance equal to 0.001 mole.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A unit equal to one-thousandth of an international unit.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A unit equal to one-thousandth of an international unit.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A dose calculation unit expressed as a number of arbitrary units of substance per one square meter of a body surface area.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A dose calculation unit expressed as a number of arbitrary units of substance per one square meter of a body surface area.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A metric unit of mass equal to one millionth of a gram or one one thousandth of a milligram.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A metric unit of mass equal to one millionth of a gram or one one thousandth of a milligram.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A unit of a mass fraction expressed as a number of micrograms of substance per kilogram of mixture. The unit is also used as a dose calculation unit.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A unit of a mass fraction expressed as a number of micrograms of substance per kilogram of mixture. The unit is also used as a dose calculation unit.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A dose calculation unit expressed in microgram(s) per kilogram per period of time equal to twenty-four hours.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A dose calculation unit expressed in microgram(s) per kilogram per period of time equal to twenty-four hours.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A dose administration rate unit where the amount of product to be delivered or administered is calculated in micrograms as a function of the subject's weight in kilograms and is delivered or administered over the time period of one week.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A dose administration rate unit where the amount of product to be delivered or administered is calculated in micrograms as a function of the subject's weight in kilograms and is delivered or administered over the time period of one week.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A metric unit of areal density equal to approximately 2.94935E-8 ounce per square yard. Also used as a dose calculation unit.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A metric unit of areal density equal to approximately 2.94935E-8 ounce per square yard. Also used as a dose calculation unit.

permissibleValues.shortMeaning: Microgram per Square Meter per Hour
permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A dose calculation unit expressed in microgram(s) per square meter per period of time equal to sixty minutes.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A dose calculation unit expressed in microgram(s) per square meter per period of time equal to sixty minutes.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: One-millionth of a liter.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A metric unit of volume equal to one millionth of a liter or one one thousandth of a milliliter.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: The unitage assigned by the WHO to International Biological Standards - substances, classed as biological according to the criteria provided by WHO Expert Committee on Biological Standardization (e.g. hormones, enzymes, and vaccines), to enable the results of biological and immunological assay procedures to be expressed in the same way throughout the world. The definition of an international unit is generally arbitrary and technical, and has to be officially approved by the International Conference for Unification of Formulae.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: The unitage assigned by the WHO to International Biological Standards - substances, classed as biological according to the criteria provided by WHO Expert Committee on Biological Standardization (e.g. hormones, enzymes, and vaccines), to enable the results of biological and immunological assay procedures to be expressed in the same way throughout the world. The definition of an international unit is generally arbitrary and technical, and has to be officially approved by the International Conference for Unification of Formulae.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: An arbitrary unit of substance content expressed in international units of biological activity per one kilogram of mass of the system. It is also used as a dose calculation unit expressed in international units of biological activity per one kilogram of body mass.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: An arbitrary unit of substance content expressed in international units of biological activity per one kilogram of mass of the system. It is also used as a dose calculation unit expressed in international units of biological activity per one kilogram of body mass.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: Unit of arbitrary substance concentration (biologic activity concentration) defined as the concentration of one international unit per one liter of the system volume.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: Unit of arbitrary substance concentration (biologic activity concentration) defined as the concentration of one international unit per one liter of the system volume.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: Unit of arbitrary substance concentration (biologic activity concentration) defined as the concentration of one international unit per one milligram of substance.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: Unit of arbitrary substance concentration (biologic activity concentration) defined as the concentration of one international unit per one milligram of substance.

permissibleValues.meaningDescription: A thin slice of material containing a medicinal agent.
permissibleValues.vmDescription: A thin slice of material containing a medicinal agent.
